  "title": "Site Executive / Site Supervisor #75665",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Waste Management</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Site Executive / Site Supervisor</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tuas (Company transport provided)</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon - Fri, 8.00am - 5.00pm; Sat, 8.00am – 12.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $2,800 + AWS + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the main contact for coordinating with internal and external parties to ensure waste collection requirements are met at customer sites</li><li>Work with customer site operations teams to understand and clarify their needs</li><li>Manage new and ongoing projects, including liaising with customers on their specifications and schedules</li><li>Track and resolve site risks and issues</li><li>Oversee workers and subcontractors at project sites, and report any issues to the Project Manager</li><li>Assist the Project Manager in managing customer care programs, including monitoring satisfaction and addressing complaints or changes</li><li>Ensure all personnel follow safety, environmental, and health policies and procedures; review work activities and job safety risk assessments (JSRA)</li><li>Train workers on new job requirements and the use of new equipment</li><li>Arrange transportation for workers to and from sites</li><li>Support worker deployment to sites in case of emergency activation (including after office hours)</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Completed Safety Orientation Course (related to power plant or construction work)</li><li>Completion of Supervise Work At Height Course (preferred)</li><li>Experience in supervising scaffolding project</li><li>Knowledge of dismantling, and maintaining scaffolding</li><li>Understanding of WSH Scaffolding Regulations and Requirements (preferred)</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#75665 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
